The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Wednesday, December 08, 2004 

 BRIEFS

 Howrah, Dec. 7: Pankaj Patra has been arrested from Bagnan for hacking to death his 26-year-old wife, Purnima, and three-year-old daughter. 

 He has confessed to the crime and police believe he suspected her of having an affair with a local youth. His elder daughter, seven-year-old Sangeeta, saw his father commit the crime and ran into a neighbours house. Alerted, they caught Patra and called in the police. 

 Calcutta: Governor-designate Gopalkrishna Gandhi will take oath of office on December 14 at 5 pm at Raj Bhavan, home secretary Amit Kiran Deb said. Gandhi takes over from Viren J. Shah, whose tenure ends on December 13. 

 Calcutta: Hosiery workers called off a strike on December 8 after a tripartite meeting at Writers? Buildings, where it was decided that the government would form a committee which will submit a report in six weeks on the terms and conditions of implementation of productivity-linked wages. 

 Midnapore: Anupam Mukherjee, 42, a maintenance technician at the Kolaghat thermal power plant died after falling from a platform in the plant around 7:30 pm on Tuesday.




